action.message:
## Summary

The bug was in `src/flb_parser.c` in the `flb_parser_time_lookup()` function at line 1202.

### Root Cause
When parsing logs that only contain time (`HH:MM:SS`) without a date component, the code uses `gmtime_r()` to extract the current date (year/month/day) from the current system time. When `Time_System_Timezone` is enabled, this gives the date in **UTC**, not in the local timezone.

For timezones ahead of UTC (e.g., Europe/Stockholm = UTC+2), times just after midnight local time (00:00–01:59) correspond to the previous day in UTC (22:00–23:59). Using `gmtime_r()` means the parser picks up the **previous day's date**, assigning logs to the wrong day.

### Fix
Changed `gmtime_r(&time_now, &tmy)` to `localtime_r(&time_now, &tmy)` when `parser->time_system_timezone` is set. This ensures the date components are extracted in the system's local timezone, matching the timezone that will be used later by `mktime()` in `flb_parser_tm2time()`.

The fix is a single conditional (4 lines changed):
```c
if (parser->time_system_timezone) {
    localtime_r(&time_now, &tmy);
}
else {
    gmtime_r(&time_now, &tmy);
}
```

### Tests Verified
- `flb-it-parser` — all 5 tests pass
- `flb-rt-filter_parser` — all 14 tests pass (including `filter_parser_use_system_timezone`)
- `flb-it-strptime` — all 13 tests pass

